claim.claim-text:
An image processing program executable by an image processing system which is configured of: an imaging unit which images a sheet of memo paper having positioning symbols and serving as an imaging object; an image acquisition unit which detects the positioning symbols from original image data imaged by the imaging unit, recognizes a predetermined area calculated based on the positioning symbols as a first range, extracts only image data existing in the first range to acquire this image data as extracted image data, and corrects the extracted image data based on the distance between the positioning symbols; and an image data storage unit which stores the extracted image data acquired by the image acquisition unit, wherein

the positioning symbols are disposed in at least two locations out of areas near four corners of a rectangular paper main portion and created as symbol codes constituted by multi-valued graphics, each of the positioning symbols has an emerging portion having a color value that is different from a ground color of the paper main portion and a non-emerging portion having the ground color of the paper main portion, the emerging portion includes a frame-shaped emerging portion having two straight line portions respectively parallel with two sides extending from a corner of the paper main portion and a corner portion where edges of the two straight line portions contact each other, and the non-emerging portion of the positioning symbol is an area having the ground color which is surrounded by the frame-shaped emerging portion, and

the imaging object further includes a second range which is located such that at least a portion of the second range is in contact with an outer perimeter of a virtual rectangle having opposing corners formed by one positioning symbol and an other positioning symbol disposed on the paper main portion, and which has line segments disposed thereon to form a plurality of squares, and

the image processing program causes a CPU to execute the steps of:
detecting the positioning symbols from original image data of the imaging object imaged by the imaging unit and including the positioning symbols disposed in at least the two predetermined locations;
recognizing a predetermined area calculated based on the detected positioning symbols as a first range;
extracting only image data existing in the first range and acquiring this image data as extracted image data;
storing the extracted image data in the image data storage unit; and
detecting a predetermined area based on the relative positional relationship between the positioning symbols, recognizing this area as a second range, and storing, as information related to image data read from the first range, predetermined information contained in an image handwritten in the second range.

An image processing method executable by an image processing system which is configured of: an imaging unit which images a sheet of memo paper having positioning symbols and serving as an imaging object; an image acquisition unit which detects the positioning symbols from original image data imaged by the imaging unit, recognizes a predetermined area calculated based on the positioning symbols as a first range, extracts only image data existing in the first range to acquire this image data as extracted image data, and corrects the extracted image data based on the distance between the positioning symbols; and an image data storage unit which stores the extracted image data acquired by the image acquisition unit, wherein

the positioning symbols are disposed in at least two locations out of areas near four corners of a rectangular paper main portion and created as symbol codes constituted by multi-valued graphics, each of the positioning symbols has an emerging portion having a color value that is different from a ground color of the paper main portion and a non-emerging portion having the ground color of the paper main portion, the emerging portion includes a frame-shaped emerging portion having two straight line portions respectively parallel with two sides extending from a corner of the paper main portion and a corner portion where edges of the two straight line portions contact each other, and the non-emerging portion of the positioning symbol is an area having the ground color which is surrounded by the frame-shaped emerging portion, and

the imaging object further includes a second range which is located such that at least a portion of the second range is in contact with an outer perimeter of a virtual rectangle having opposing corners formed by one positioning symbol and an other positioning symbol disposed on the paper main portion, and which has line segments disposed thereon to form a plurality of squares, and

the image processing method comprises the steps executed by a CPU of:
detecting the positioning symbols from original image data of the imaging object imaged by the imaging unit and including the positioning symbols disposed in at least the two predetermined locations;
recognizing a predetermined area calculated based on the detected positioning symbols as a first range;
extracting only image data existing in the first range and acquiring this image data as extracted image data;
storing the extracted image data in the image data storage unit; and
detecting a predetermined area based on the relative positional relationship between the positioning symbols, recognizing this area as a second range, and storing, as information related to image data read from the first range, predetermined information contained in an image handwritten in the second range.
